                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1271-2">Plusieurs biographies, en prose et en vers, sont mentionnees dans BHO, 383-86.
Details, references et histoire du couvent, qui fut un temps residence des patriarches,
ou fut fonde, dans Ia premiere moitie du XIX• siecle, Ia congregation des moines
chaldeens antonins "de saint Hormizdas" , et qui fournit une pleiade
de copistes, dans Fiey, Assyrie chretienne, II, 533-48.
Hoffmann, Ausziige, 19-22.
BSO, II, 167- 69 (J. Rabbi).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1271">Rabban Hormizd was a monastic founder of the
          Church of the East who lived under the Patriarch Isho-yaw II. He spent 32 years at the
          monastery of Bar 'Idta, and then he and other monks left and founded an important
          monastery near Mosul, north of Alqosh.</note>
